  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why did my guy friend ask me if I have a boyfriend or not?",
  "response": "When a guy friend asks if you have a boyfriend, it could be for several reasons:\n\n1. **Interest in Dating You**: He might be interested in you romantically and is checking to see if you're available. This is often a subtle way to gauge whether it's safe to pursue you without stepping on someone else's toes.\n\n2. **Curiosity or Casual Conversation**: Sometimes, it's just a way to keep the conversation going or to learn more about your life. People often ask about relationship status as part of getting to know someone better.\n\n3. **Setting Up a Friend**: He might know someone who he thinks would be a good match for you and is checking your availability before playing matchmaker.\n\n4. **Clarifying Boundaries**: If your interactions have been flirty or ambiguous, he might ask to clarify the nature of your relationship and set appropriate boundaries.\n\n5. **General Social Inquiry**: In some social contexts, asking about someone\u2019s relationship status is a common and non-intrusive way to gather information about a person\u2019s life.\n\nUnderstanding the context of the conversation and your friend's behavior towards you can help you better interpret his intentions. If you're unsure, you can always ask him directly why he wanted to know or steer the conversation to see if he hints at his intentions.",
